Java 8 Installation Step by Step

Step 1: Download
Download Java Development Kit from this Link: 
https://www.oracle.com/in/java/technologies/javase/javase8-archive-downloads.html
Login to oracle account to download setup file (or Create a new account if you dont have).

Step 2: Installation
Once the download is complete, locate the downloaded file and double-click to run the installer.
Follow the onscreen instruction to complete the setup.

Step 3: Verification
After install go to C drive and verify below path (64 bit) it is installed or not.
C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.8.0_xxx

Step 4: Setting Environmental Variable
Click Windows key+s and search 'environment' Click Edit environment variables (windows 10)
Or Open System Properties
Under the window goto advanced tab and click Environment Variables
In System variable click New button and add “JAVA_HOME” as variable name and Java installation directory i.e. C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.8.0_202 as Variable value and hit OK button.
If variable name PATH exists edit the variable and add 'C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.8.0_202/bin' as variable value. Otherwise click New button and create varible PATH.

Step 5: Test Configuration
Open Command prompt and type java -version
It will show the version of jdk installed on the system.
